2026 Regular Session ENROLLED
SENATE RESOLUTION NO. 142
BY SENATOR HODGES
A RESOLUTION
To commend and congratulate Braxton Whitesell on being named reserve champion of the
Hondo Rodeo Fest in New Orleans, Louisiana.
WHEREAS, Braxton Whitesell, a proud resident of the city of Walker in Livingston
Parish, Louisiana, has demonstrated exceptional talent, discipline, and determination in the
sport of rodeo; and
WHEREAS, Braxton has distinguished himself as a dedicated athlete and
representative of his community through years of hard work and commitment to excellence;
and
WHEREAS, Braxton has compiled an extraordinary list of accomplishments in high
school rodeo, including being crowned champion bull rider at the International Finals Youth
Rodeo in 2025; placing sixth in bull riding at the 2025 National High School Finals Rodeo,
as well as qualifying in 2022, 2023, and 2024; winning three Mississippi High School Rodeo
Association bull riding championships, two Mississippi High School Rodeo Association
saddle bronc riding championships, and being named the 2025 Tri-State Rodeo High School
Champion; and
WHEREAS, Braxton Whitesell has also excelled at the professional level through
the Professional Cowboys Rodeo Association, currently sitting ninth in the world standings,
leading the Resistol Rookie of the year all-around standings, placing second in the Resistol
Rookie of the Year bull riding competition, earning first place at the Fort Worth Stock Show
and Rodeo Rookie Rally and the Brighton Field Days Festival Extreme Bulls event, and
earning third place at the Dixie National Rodeo; and
WHEREAS, in 2026, Braxton Whitesell earned the prestigious title of reserve
champion at the Hondo Rodeo Fest in New Orleans, Louisiana, one of the region's most
competitive and respected rodeo events; and
WHEREAS, this remarkable achievement brings great pride and recognition to
Livingston Parish and the city of Walker, showcasing the strength, character, skill, and
perseverance of its young athletes; and
